Venezuelan President  Hugo Chavez ,
speaking on state television from a campaign rally in Bolivar
state, said he had approved $300 million for electricity
projects in the state.  The projects include a power transmission line from Guri to
Ciudad Bolivar, the state capital, and three power substations
in the city, Chavez said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
